00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:24,240
I'm thankful that our God is the God of all comfort,

261
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:26,800
we read that in 2 Corinthians chapter number one,

262
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:28,280
and what a blessing to know

263
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:30,280
that he is the God of all comfort,

264
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:33,900
but he brings comfort, he brings to the heart of his people.

265
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:35,600
Listen, remember Jesus said this,

266
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:38,640
let not your heart be troubled.

267
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:41,700
There are times in which you face circumstances

268
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:45,760
and situations in life that you can have a troubled heart.

269
00:11:45,760 --> 00:11:48,040
The circumstances by which Jesus Christ

270
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:50,640
gave that statement to those disciples

271
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:52,520
was the fact that he let them know

272
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:55,080
he would soon go to the cross of Calvary,

273
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:57,800
and he explained to them all that would come to pass

274
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,760
in those days ahead, and he says,

275
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:02,520
let not your heart be troubled.

276
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:06,100
He goes on, in fact, turn over to John, if you will,

277
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:09,340
in chapter number 14, because we find a couple of verses

278
00:12:09,340 --> 00:12:11,920
that we'll look within this text of Scripture

279
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:15,160
with regard to how God's presence brings us comfort.

280
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:18,640
He tells them not to be troubled.

281
00:12:18,640 --> 00:12:20,920
We find that as he continues to develop the thought

282
00:12:20,920 --> 00:12:23,080
throughout the passage and throughout

283
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:24,480
these couple of chapters.

284
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:28,420
Notice, if you will, in verse number 16 of John 14.

285
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,120
And I want you to consider with me

286
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:36,620
the reality of these disciples that Jesus is speaking to

287
00:12:36,620 --> 00:12:38,840
and the way in which they had an opportunity

288
00:12:38,840 --> 00:12:43,160
to walk with Christ personally during his earthly ministry.

289
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:44,440
It was a unique opportunity

290
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:46,240
that these men had at this season.

291
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,920
In fact, there's only a certain generation of people

292
00:12:48,920 --> 00:12:52,480
that ever had the opportunity to see as an eyewitness

293
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:56,120
to the Lord Jesus Christ and his ministry and walk with him.

294
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:58,480
And these disciples had that opportunity

295
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:01,440
and Jesus is speaking to them.

296
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:03,680
And he tells them this in verse number 16,

297
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:06,120
and I will pray the Father

298
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:10,320
and he shall give you another comforter

299
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:12,040
that he may abide with you.

300
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:13,480
What does it say?

301
00:13:13,480 --> 00:13:14,860
Forever.

302
00:13:14,860 --> 00:13:19,420
Verse 17, as he continues, even the spirit of truth

303
00:13:19,420 --> 00:13:21,680
whom the world cannot receive

304
00:13:21,680 --> 00:13:24,780
because it seeth him not, neither knoweth him,

305
00:13:24,780 --> 00:13:27,080
but ye know him for he dwelleth with you

306
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:30,080
and he shall be in you.

307
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:31,440
In verse 18, the Bible says,

308
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:36,440
I will not leave you comfortless, I will come to you.

309
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:39,440
Now, it's often throughout the scriptures,

310
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:40,960
throughout the gospels,

311
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:43,640
there's many references that you find

312
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:45,760
that really prove the deity of Christ.

313
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:49,940
Passages of scripture that maybe aren't the top tier,

314
00:13:49,940 --> 00:13:51,400
if you will, that you would go to,

315
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:53,520
but it's interesting because it says here

316
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:55,000
that he's gonna send the comforter,

317
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:57,280
I'll give you another comforter in verse 16.

318
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:59,920
And verse 18, he says, I will come to you.

319
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:01,880
And we find as we begin to look here

320
00:14:01,880 --> 00:14:04,500
at the truth of the Trinity,

321
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:07,920
the fact that God, the Father, God, the Son,

322
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:11,120
God, the Holy Spirit, here within the context,

323
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:14,520
we find that Jesus is speaking to these disciples

324
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:18,640
and he's telling them about the Holy Spirit of God,

325
00:14:18,640 --> 00:14:21,960
the comforter, the spirit of truth.

326
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:24,700
We sometimes see him referred to as the Holy Ghost

327
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:26,680
and sometimes as the Holy Spirit,

328
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:28,200
but we find here that he says

329
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:31,700
that he may abide with you forever.

330
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:34,880
See, Jesus Christ was with them at that particular time.

331
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:36,880
And again, it was a unique opportunity

332
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:39,240
for those that were living at that time

333
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:42,320
and for these 12 that we would refer to as disciples

334
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:46,560
to be able to have that opportunity to walk with Christ.

335
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:48,200
But we have the Holy Spirit.

336
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:51,600
At the moment that you trust that Jesus Christ

337
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,160
is your personal savior,

338
00:14:53,160 --> 00:14:56,080
the Holy Spirit of God came in and took up residence.

339
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:59,220
Your body is the temple of the Holy Ghost.

340
00:14:59,220 --> 00:15:02,060
And we find that in 1 Corinthians chapter number six,

341
00:15:02,060 --> 00:15:04,360
and we can rejoice in understanding

342
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:06,280
that Jesus is giving this truth.

343
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:08,240
And as he gives the truth,

344
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:12,260
he's speaking specifically about his presence,

345
00:15:12,260 --> 00:15:15,320
giving comfort and refers to the Holy Spirit

346
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:17,200
as the comforter.

347
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:19,040
Look, if you will, in chapter 16

348
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:20,700
and look at verse number seven.

349
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:23,660
Again, as he continues to have this discourse

350
00:15:23,660 --> 00:15:27,620
with his disciples leading to his crucifixion,

351
00:15:27,620 --> 00:15:30,380
we find in verse number seven of chapter 16,

352
00:15:30,380 --> 00:15:34,180
it says, nevertheless, I tell you the truth.

353
00:15:34,180 --> 00:15:38,480
It is expedient for you that I go away.

354
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:39,960
Now understand with me,

355
00:15:39,960 --> 00:15:42,240
the disciples weren't exactly excited

356
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:45,320
about the fact that Jesus was gonna go away.

357
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:48,800
The reality is that there were a bunch of discourse

358
00:15:48,800 --> 00:15:51,640
and things that take place throughout the text of scripture

359
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:54,040
and they're dealing with this trying time,

360
00:15:54,040 --> 00:15:55,360
this difficult time,

361
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:59,920
but Jesus says it is expedient for you that I go away.

362
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:01,000
Notice the rest of the verse,

363
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:03,120
for if I go not away,

364
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:06,860
the comforter will not come unto you,

365
00:16:06,860 --> 00:16:11,100
but if I depart, I will send him unto you.

366
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:13,780
I'm thankful for the ministry of the Holy Spirit of God,

367
00:16:13,780 --> 00:16:15,180
the Holy Ghost.

368
00:16:15,180 --> 00:16:16,420
I'm thankful this morning

369
00:16:16,420 --> 00:16:18,980
that he is the earnest of our inheritance,

370
00:16:18,980 --> 00:16:21,740
that his spirit just,

371
00:16:21,740 --> 00:16:24,360
it's a wonderful truth that we have

372
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:26,140
as New Testament believers.

373
00:16:26,140 --> 00:16:28,980
His spirit bears witness with our spirit.

374
00:16:28,980 --> 00:16:30,900
And we find this morning

375
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:33,140
that as you look at the whole of scripture,

376
00:16:33,140 --> 00:16:35,160
that yes, there's times in which you look

377
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:37,300
at the Old Testament where the Spirit of God

378
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:39,380
would come upon individuals,

379
00:16:39,380 --> 00:16:40,980
but then you would find that there were times

380
00:16:41,860 --> 00:16:42,700
in which the Spirit of God

381
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:43,940
would depart from those individuals.

382
00:16:43,940 --> 00:16:46,700
And we find this morning that we have the truth

383
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:49,220
and the promise that the Holy Spirit

384
00:16:49,220 --> 00:16:53,100
is indwelling us as the people of God.

385
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:56,180
And what a blessing, the comforter has come.

386
00:16:56,180 --> 00:16:58,060
We sing sometimes that wonderful hymn

387
00:16:58,060 --> 00:16:59,940
and what a great truth it is.

388
00:16:59,940 --> 00:17:02,140
And we find this morning,

389
00:17:02,140 --> 00:17:04,820
this truth of God's presence bringing comfort.

390
00:17:04,820 --> 00:17:07,180
Look, if you will, I mentioned earlier, Hebrews,

391
00:17:07,180 --> 00:17:09,180
look at Hebrews chapter 13, if you will,

392
00:17:09,180 --> 00:17:10,620
Hebrews chapter 13,

393
00:17:11,260 --> 00:17:12,700
and we look at these two verses of scripture,

394
00:17:12,700 --> 00:17:15,620
many times we simply quote the last part

395
00:17:15,620 --> 00:17:17,180
of verse number five.

396
00:17:17,180 --> 00:17:18,780
I will never leave thee nor forsake thee.

397
00:17:18,780 --> 00:17:21,020
And it's not inappropriate that we would quote

398
00:17:21,020 --> 00:17:22,100
that part of the verse,

399
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:24,180
but I want you to look within context

400
00:17:24,180 --> 00:17:28,100
here in Hebrews 13, verses five and six.

401
00:17:28,100 --> 00:17:30,380
And we look at these two verses of scripture

402
00:17:30,380 --> 00:17:32,860
and we find that there's great truth

403
00:17:32,860 --> 00:17:34,900
that is revealed to us as the people of God.

404
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:37,420
Notice in verse number five of Hebrews 13,

405
00:17:37,420 --> 00:17:40,060
the Bible says, let your conversation

406
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:43,100
be without covetousness.

407
00:17:43,100 --> 00:17:44,700
Now there's a whole sermon that you could preach

408
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:46,500
right there on that verse of scripture.

409
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:50,220
We live in a world that is a world that covets.

410
00:17:50,220 --> 00:17:54,380
We live in a society that tries to approach you and me

411
00:17:54,380 --> 00:17:56,220
and all those within its culture

412
00:17:56,220 --> 00:17:58,340
to be someone that covets.

413
00:17:58,340 --> 00:18:01,300
I need this, I need more, so on and so forth.

414
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:02,820
But he says, let your conversation,

415
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:07,500
your behavior, your lifestyle be without covetousness.

416
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:10,680
And then he says this, and be content

417
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:13,840
with such things as you have.

418
00:18:13,840 --> 00:18:16,340
Paul said that he's learned in what sort of state he is

419
00:18:16,340 --> 00:18:19,860
to be content and God's people are to be content,

420
00:18:19,860 --> 00:18:21,380
not to be covetous.

421
00:18:21,380 --> 00:18:23,380
And we find here that he says,

422
00:18:23,380 --> 00:18:26,660
in the context of speaking about covetousness

423
00:18:26,660 --> 00:18:29,780
and contrasting it with being content and having contentment,

424
00:18:29,820 --> 00:18:32,860
he says this, be content with such things as you have,

425
00:18:32,860 --> 00:18:37,760
for he hath said, I will never leave thee nor forsake thee.

426
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:40,120
Isn't that precious?

427
00:18:41,060 --> 00:18:43,940
Why is it that we should not be covetous?

428
00:18:43,940 --> 00:18:45,900
Why is it that we should be content?

429
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:48,380
Because we have the presence of God

430
00:18:48,380 --> 00:18:50,500
and it gives us comfort.

431
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:53,340
We find, we talk about that song,

432
00:18:53,340 --> 00:18:57,100
count your blessings that money cannot buy.

433
00:18:57,100 --> 00:18:59,580
Listen, there are a lot of people that are looking

434
00:19:00,340 --> 00:19:01,540
and they think they can throw money at things

435
00:19:01,540 --> 00:19:04,860
to be able to get, listen, you can't buy comfort.

436
00:19:04,860 --> 00:19:06,620
The Holy Spirit of God is the comforter

437
00:19:06,620 --> 00:19:08,860
and our God is the God of all comfort.

438
00:19:08,860 --> 00:19:11,220
And he can give us comfort in the time

439
00:19:11,220 --> 00:19:13,540
of great trouble and difficulty.

440
00:19:13,540 --> 00:19:16,420
And then we find verse number six as a response really

441
00:19:16,420 --> 00:19:18,540
to the truth that is given to us

442
00:19:18,540 --> 00:19:19,900
at the end of verse number five,

443
00:19:19,900 --> 00:19:21,620
I will never leave thee nor forsake thee

444
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:24,980
so that we may boldly say,

445
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:29,420
the Lord is my helper.

446
00:19:30,260 --> 00:19:32,580
And I will not fear what man shall do unto me.

447
00:19:32,580 --> 00:19:34,260
That gives us comfort.

448
00:19:34,260 --> 00:19:37,260
And also as we would bridge into the next point

449
00:19:37,260 --> 00:19:38,740
of our message this morning,

450
00:19:38,740 --> 00:19:40,740
not only does God's presence bring comfort,

451
00:19:40,740 --> 00:19:43,740
but God's presence brings courage.

452
00:19:43,740 --> 00:19:46,980
So you notice in verse number five and six of Hebrews 13,

453
00:19:46,980 --> 00:19:51,220
not only the truth of the Holy Spirit bringing comfort

454
00:19:51,220 --> 00:19:54,100
and that we can say the Lord is my helper.

455
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:57,620
Can you imagine the amount of comfort that gives us?

456
00:19:57,620 --> 00:19:59,740
And we understand the Lord is my helper.

457
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:02,300
The one who created all things,

458
00:20:02,300 --> 00:20:03,940
the one who said, let there be light,

459
00:20:03,940 --> 00:20:06,580
he is my helper, the divine helper,

460
00:20:06,580 --> 00:20:08,980
the one that's available, the one that's able.

461
00:20:08,980 --> 00:20:11,740
And we find that it says, and I will not fear,

462
00:20:11,740 --> 00:20:14,820
again, bridging really between the two thoughts this morning

463
00:20:14,820 --> 00:20:17,020
that God's presence brings comfort,

464
00:20:17,020 --> 00:20:19,340
but number two, God's presence brings courage

465
00:20:19,340 --> 00:20:24,180
because I can say, I will not fear what man shall do.

466
00:20:24,180 --> 00:20:26,460
I will only say the Lord's my helper

467
00:20:26,460 --> 00:20:31,460
and I will not fear what man shall do unto me, that courage.

468
00:20:33,020 --> 00:20:34,700
We see comfort, but number two,

469
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:36,560
we see God's presence brings courage.

470
00:20:36,560 --> 00:20:38,660
You know, we need people of courage today,

471
00:20:39,580 --> 00:20:44,580
people of courage to do what God has called us to do.

472
00:20:44,580 --> 00:20:47,880
To be courageous doesn't mean that you have no fear.

473
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:50,340
To be courageous doesn't mean it's gonna be simple.

474
00:20:50,340 --> 00:20:52,340
It just simply means that we believe God

475
00:20:52,340 --> 00:20:55,900
and that we're going to do what God's called us to do.

476
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:57,260
Look, if you will, in the book of Joshua,

477
00:20:57,260 --> 00:20:58,280
look at a couple of examples.

478
00:20:58,280 --> 00:20:59,340
Actually, go back to Genesis.

479
00:20:59,340 --> 00:21:00,460
We'll start in Genesis.

480
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:02,540
And let's look at a couple of examples this morning

481
00:21:02,540 --> 00:21:06,500
of individual believers that were told about God's presence

482
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:08,700
and how it gave them courage

483
00:21:08,700 --> 00:21:11,440
to do what God had called them to do.

484
00:21:13,020 --> 00:21:15,820
I believe that God has a plan for each of us.

485
00:21:15,820 --> 00:21:17,900
I believe that God's plan is perfect

486
00:21:17,900 --> 00:21:20,820
and I believe that we need to know God's plan

487
00:21:20,820 --> 00:21:23,540
and seek to do God's plan to fulfill it.

488
00:21:23,540 --> 00:21:25,740
And I believe that as you look throughout the scriptures

489
00:21:26,580 --> 00:21:28,380
that we'll look at a number of men this morning

490
00:21:28,380 --> 00:21:30,960
that had been given an assignment, if you will,

491
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:33,340
or would be assigned a task,

492
00:21:33,340 --> 00:21:38,340
and God reminds them and reassures them of his presence

493
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:41,660
and it would give them courage to be able to carry out

494
00:21:41,660 --> 00:21:43,920
what God called them to do.

495
00:21:43,920 --> 00:21:46,980
Jacob, here in Genesis chapter 46,

496
00:21:46,980 --> 00:21:49,100
we find that he's been told

497
00:21:49,100 --> 00:21:51,080
at this particular time in his life,

498
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:53,320
he had thought that his son had been killed

499
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:55,020
and he believed that he was dead,

500
00:21:55,020 --> 00:21:57,220
but he finds out that Joseph is alive

501
00:21:57,220 --> 00:22:00,300
and we find that Joseph had sent the brothers back

502
00:22:00,300 --> 00:22:03,020
and sent them with the wagons and all the things

503
00:22:03,020 --> 00:22:06,420
and with the instruction of coming back to Egypt

504
00:22:06,420 --> 00:22:08,580
and bringing dad with them and all those things.

505
00:22:08,580 --> 00:22:12,180
And we come to Genesis chapter 46.

506
00:22:12,180 --> 00:22:13,900
The Bible says in verse number one,

507
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:16,260
and Israel took his journey with all that he had

508
00:22:16,260 --> 00:22:19,300
and came to Beersheba and offered sacrifices

509
00:22:19,300 --> 00:22:22,300
unto the God of his father, Isaac.

510
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:23,680
The Bible tells us in verse number two,

511
00:22:23,680 --> 00:22:26,920
when God spake unto Israel in the visions of the night

512
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:30,280
and said, Jacob, Jacob, and he said, here am I.

513
00:22:31,360 --> 00:22:34,920
Notice what God says beginning in verse number three.

514
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:37,760
He starts out by saying, I am God.

515
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:39,400
Isn't that good?

516
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:42,220
I am God.

517
00:22:42,220 --> 00:22:45,160
That's how God begins to speak to Jacob.

518
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:47,240
And he says, the God of thy father,

519
00:22:48,320 --> 00:22:52,320
fear not to go down into Egypt.

520
00:22:53,280 --> 00:22:57,560
We find that Jacob does not voice his fear

521
00:22:57,560 --> 00:23:00,640
as far as we have written within the canon of scripture,

522
00:23:00,640 --> 00:23:03,160
but God knows your heart and he knows my heart.

523
00:23:04,040 --> 00:23:08,080
And he tells Jacob to fear not because Jacob was fearful.

524
00:23:08,080 --> 00:23:10,680
He says, fear not to go down into Egypt

525
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:14,920
for I will there make of thee a great nation.

526
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:16,160
Notice in verse number four,

527
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:21,160
I will go down with thee into Egypt.

528
00:23:21,160 --> 00:23:23,100
Isn't that precious?

529
00:23:23,100 --> 00:23:25,280
That God says to Jacob,

530
00:23:25,280 --> 00:23:27,520
he doesn't just tell him to fear not.

531
00:23:27,520 --> 00:23:28,440
He doesn't just tell him

532
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:30,160
that he's gonna build a great nation there,

533
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:35,160
but he says, I will go down with thee into Egypt.

534
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:38,360
And I will also surely bring thee up again

535
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:42,920
