539
00:23:51,960 --> 00:23:54,740
He says, I will go down with thee into Egypt.

540
00:23:54,740 --> 00:23:57,540
And Jacob, we know as you would continue to read,

541
00:23:57,540 --> 00:24:02,180
you find that he comes and indeed he enters into Egypt

542
00:24:02,180 --> 00:24:04,660
and we find later in the text of scripture

543
00:24:04,660 --> 00:24:08,340
that as they come, there's a great reunion and embracing

544
00:24:08,340 --> 00:24:11,740
that he says this in verse number 30 of the same chapter

545
00:24:11,740 --> 00:24:13,180
and Israel said unto Joseph,

546
00:24:13,180 --> 00:24:17,340
now let me die since I have seen thy face

547
00:24:17,340 --> 00:24:19,160
because thou are yet alive.

548
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:20,860
The Bible says that he fell on his neck

549
00:24:21,660 --> 00:24:24,340
in verse 29 and wept on his neck a good while.

550
00:24:24,340 --> 00:24:26,540
It was a sweet reunion, a sweet embrace,

551
00:24:26,540 --> 00:24:28,560
but I want you to be mindful of the fact

552
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:32,020
that as he was given this really responsibility,

553
00:24:32,020 --> 00:24:34,700
this opportunity to go to Egypt, he's fearful.

554
00:24:34,700 --> 00:24:36,420
He's in the place at this time

555
00:24:36,420 --> 00:24:39,020
where God had promised him a land

556
00:24:39,020 --> 00:24:41,700
and God's saying, go down into Egypt.

557
00:24:41,700 --> 00:24:44,120
And he says, I will go down with thee.

558
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:46,700
What a blessing to know the presence of God,

559
00:24:47,700 --> 00:24:52,140
to truly know the comfort that comes,

560
00:24:52,140 --> 00:24:54,940
the courage that comes because why?

561
00:24:54,940 --> 00:24:56,780
God is with me.

562
00:24:56,780 --> 00:24:58,100
Thou art with me.

563
00:24:58,100 --> 00:25:00,020
Notice, if you will, the life of Joshua.

564
00:25:00,020 --> 00:25:02,380
Turn to Joshua chapter number one, if you would.

565
00:25:02,380 --> 00:25:03,740
In Joshua chapter number one,

566
00:25:03,740 --> 00:25:05,780
we fast forward in Israel's history

567
00:25:05,780 --> 00:25:08,020
and we see that there's much that's taking place

568
00:25:08,020 --> 00:25:10,900
and the wilderness wanderings have been fulfilled.

569
00:25:10,900 --> 00:25:13,340
We looked at Jacob, they're going down into Egypt.

570
00:25:13,340 --> 00:25:15,480
They'd be there and they'd be delivered

571
00:25:15,480 --> 00:25:18,040
through the Egyptian bondage

572
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:20,960
and we understand their deliverance in the book of Exodus.

573
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:25,280
We read of that following their deliverance.

574
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:27,060
You read of their wilderness wanderings

575
00:25:27,060 --> 00:25:30,840
and we understand that Moses would not be permitted

576
00:25:30,840 --> 00:25:33,520
to take, to lead as the human leader,

577
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:35,760
the children of Israel into the land of promise

578
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:38,240
and God raises up Joshua.

579
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:39,440
And it's precious to me

580
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:41,580
as you enter into the book of Joshua,

581
00:25:41,580 --> 00:25:43,480
you find that the book provides us

582
00:25:43,480 --> 00:25:46,840
with just a wonderful account historically

583
00:25:46,840 --> 00:25:49,120
of what took place with the children of Israel

584
00:25:49,120 --> 00:25:52,720
entering into, conquering and inhabiting the land.

585
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:54,320
But there's a beautiful picture

586
00:25:54,320 --> 00:25:55,960
throughout the book of Joshua

587
00:25:55,960 --> 00:25:58,840
of really victorious Christian living

588
00:25:58,840 --> 00:26:00,200
and how we can have victory.

589
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:02,040
I'm thankful this morning that we can have victory

590
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:03,840
through our Lord Jesus Christ.

591
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:09,300
We find here that as the task would be assigned

592
00:26:09,300 --> 00:26:13,580
and no doubt a serious responsibility

593
00:26:13,580 --> 00:26:15,420
that is given to Joshua,

594
00:26:15,420 --> 00:26:17,660
we begin reading in Joshua chapter number one

595
00:26:17,660 --> 00:26:20,340
and you find that here within the text of scripture,

596
00:26:20,340 --> 00:26:21,900
God is going to reassure

597
00:26:21,900 --> 00:26:24,980
and to promise Joshua of his presence.

598
00:26:24,980 --> 00:26:26,620
Notice with me, if you will,

599
00:26:26,620 --> 00:26:27,740
beginning in verse number one,

600
00:26:27,740 --> 00:26:29,340
we'll read just the first nine verses,

601
00:26:29,340 --> 00:26:30,540
but the Bible says this.

602
00:26:30,540 --> 00:26:34,260
Now, after the death of Moses, the servant of the Lord,

603
00:26:34,260 --> 00:26:37,300
it came to pass that the Lord spake unto Joshua,

604
00:26:37,300 --> 00:26:41,300
the son of Nun, Moses' minister saying,

605
00:26:41,300 --> 00:26:43,580
Moses, my servant is dead.

606
00:26:43,580 --> 00:26:47,180
Now therefore rise, go over this Jordan,

607
00:26:47,180 --> 00:26:49,820
thou and all this people unto the land,

608
00:26:49,820 --> 00:26:53,020
which I do give to them, even to the children of Israel.

609
00:26:53,020 --> 00:26:55,660
Every place that the sole of your foot shall tread upon,

610
00:26:55,660 --> 00:26:59,580
that have I given unto you, as I said unto Moses.

611
00:26:59,580 --> 00:27:01,260
From the wilderness and this Lebanon,

612
00:27:01,260 --> 00:27:04,020
even under the great river, the river Euphrates,

613
00:27:04,020 --> 00:27:05,500
all the land of the Hittites

614
00:27:05,540 --> 00:27:08,980
and unto the great sea toward the going down of the sun

615
00:27:08,980 --> 00:27:11,100
shall be your coast.

616
00:27:11,100 --> 00:27:12,580
Now notice verse five,

617
00:27:12,580 --> 00:27:15,700
there shall not any man be able to stand before thee

618
00:27:15,700 --> 00:27:18,340
all the days of thy life.

619
00:27:18,340 --> 00:27:23,340
As I was with Moses, so I will be with thee.

620
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:27,420
I will not fail thee nor forsake thee.

621
00:27:27,420 --> 00:27:28,820
Isn't that wonderful?

622
00:27:28,820 --> 00:27:32,260
See, did Joshua know that God was with Moses?

623
00:27:32,260 --> 00:27:33,260
Sure he did.

624
00:27:33,260 --> 00:27:36,420
I mean, Moses, remember he spent time with God.

625
00:27:36,420 --> 00:27:37,260
He was on the Mount

626
00:27:37,260 --> 00:27:39,420
and he had those opportunities to spend time with God,

627
00:27:39,420 --> 00:27:41,620
so much so that he had to put that veil on, right?

628
00:27:41,620 --> 00:27:44,220
Because his face shone and you see all of that.

629
00:27:44,220 --> 00:27:46,780
And Joshua was the minister of Moses.

630
00:27:46,780 --> 00:27:48,660
We read that in verse number one.

631
00:27:48,660 --> 00:27:50,460
And if you look in the book of Deuteronomy

632
00:27:50,460 --> 00:27:51,280
and other portions,

633
00:27:51,280 --> 00:27:54,140
you begin to see that role that Joshua had.

634
00:27:54,140 --> 00:27:57,800
And so Joshua was aware of the fact that God was with Moses,

635
00:27:57,800 --> 00:28:02,060
but God says to Joshua, as I was with Moses,

636
00:28:02,060 --> 00:28:04,920
so I will be with thee.

637
00:28:06,200 --> 00:28:09,260
I will not fail thee nor forsake thee.

638
00:28:09,260 --> 00:28:10,100
So what does he tell him?

639
00:28:10,100 --> 00:28:12,220
What is the impact, if you will?

640
00:28:12,220 --> 00:28:13,940
God's presence brings comfort,

641
00:28:13,940 --> 00:28:15,580
but God's presence brings courage.

642
00:28:15,580 --> 00:28:16,980
Notice in verse number six,

643
00:28:16,980 --> 00:28:20,140
be strong and of a good courage.

644
00:28:20,140 --> 00:28:22,920
For unto this people shalt thou divide for an inheritance,

645
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:26,620
the land which I swear under their fathers to give them.

646
00:28:26,620 --> 00:28:30,500
Only be thou strong and very courageous

647
00:28:30,500 --> 00:28:34,020
that thou mayest observe to do according to all the law,

648
00:28:34,020 --> 00:28:36,060
which Moses my servant commanded thee,

649
00:28:36,060 --> 00:28:38,940
turn not from it to the right hand or to the left,

650
00:28:38,940 --> 00:28:42,180
that thou mayest prosper whithersoever thou goest.

651
00:28:42,180 --> 00:28:43,700
Verse eight is a familiar verse.

652
00:28:43,700 --> 00:28:47,700
This book of the law shall not depart out of thy mouth,

653
00:28:47,700 --> 00:28:50,800
but thou shalt meditate therein day and night

654
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:53,400
that thou mayest observe to do according to all

655
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:54,820
that is written therein.

656
00:28:54,820 --> 00:28:57,420
For then thou shalt make thy way prosperous

657
00:28:57,420 --> 00:29:00,220
and then thou shalt have good success.

658
00:29:00,940 --> 00:29:03,980
Verse nine, have not I commanded thee?

659
00:29:03,980 --> 00:29:06,740
Be strong and of a good courage.

660
00:29:06,740 --> 00:29:09,540
Be not afraid, neither be thou dismayed.

661
00:29:09,540 --> 00:29:13,300
For the Lord thy God is with thee,

662
00:29:13,300 --> 00:29:16,220
whithersoever thou goest.

663
00:29:17,740 --> 00:29:21,100
This charge that's given to Joshua at the beginning,

664
00:29:21,100 --> 00:29:24,920
the opening of this book that contains so much history

665
00:29:24,920 --> 00:29:29,920
and so many exciting portions and exciting miracles of God

666
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:32,600
as they entered into the land and possessed the land,

667
00:29:32,600 --> 00:29:35,800
we find that God on two occasions between verse five

668
00:29:35,800 --> 00:29:38,680
and verse number nine, reassures his man,

669
00:29:38,680 --> 00:29:41,560
his servant of his presence.

670
00:29:42,620 --> 00:29:46,000
Joshua was one of those that went and spied the land,

671
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:47,320
was he not?

672
00:29:47,320 --> 00:29:51,080
We read of the 12 spies and we sing the song with the kids

673
00:29:51,080 --> 00:29:53,480
that 10 were bad and two were good.

674
00:29:53,480 --> 00:29:56,960
And those two good spies are Joshua and Caleb.

675
00:29:56,960 --> 00:29:59,880
And Joshua, in fact, not only at that particular.

676
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:03,720
but even later as he's encouraging various tribes

677
00:30:03,720 --> 00:30:07,200
to possess the land that God has given to them.

678
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:11,720
He never doubts the difficulties that would be faced.

679
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:15,680
He never dismisses the realities of life,

680
00:30:15,680 --> 00:30:19,920
but he simply says God is with us and that God is able.

681
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:22,040
It gives courage, God's presence.

682
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:24,920
See, when those 10 spies said there are cities

683
00:30:24,920 --> 00:30:26,960
that are fortified, there are walled cities,

684
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:30,240
there are giants in the land, the sons of Anak are there,

685
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:33,020
and he says all of those things, these 10 spies,

686
00:30:33,020 --> 00:30:36,180
Joshua and Caleb do not deny the report.

687
00:30:37,160 --> 00:30:38,120
Why?

688
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:40,200
Because it was a true report.

689
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:44,840
They saw the walled cities, they observed the giants,

690
00:30:44,840 --> 00:30:47,780
the sons of Anak, but they had a perspective

691
00:30:47,780 --> 00:30:50,480
that was different, and that was that our God is able.

692
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:53,360
Our God is able.

693
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:56,520
And here is Joshua, after all of that period

694
00:30:56,520 --> 00:30:59,220
of wilderness wanderings is now going to be,

695
00:30:59,220 --> 00:31:02,560
I don't think he knew in Numbers 13 and 14

696
00:31:02,560 --> 00:31:04,960
when he went to spy, I don't think he knew

697
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:07,040
that he would be the human man that would lead

698
00:31:07,040 --> 00:31:10,400
the children of Israel into the land of promise.

699
00:31:10,400 --> 00:31:13,280
But here he is, given this great task,

700
00:31:13,280 --> 00:31:14,960
this great responsibility.

701
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:16,780
Yes, it was God that would do the work,

702
00:31:16,780 --> 00:31:19,800
but there was a human leader, and his name is Joshua,

703
00:31:19,800 --> 00:31:21,840
and God says, I'm with you.

704
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:26,560
And he reassures him of his presence.

705
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:29,280
And I believe that as you look through the book of Joshua,

706
00:31:29,280 --> 00:31:30,800
you begin to see the courage, and again,

707
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:33,060
it's repeated in these verses of Scripture

708
00:31:33,060 --> 00:31:35,480
to be courageous, to have courage,

709
00:31:35,480 --> 00:31:37,880
and we find that it's the truth, the reality

710
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:40,880
of God's presence that would allow for God's man

711
00:31:40,880 --> 00:31:45,720
to have courage to carry out the task that's been assigned.

712
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:50,240
Jeremiah, if you would, turn over to the book of Jeremiah,

713
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:51,520
chapter number one.

