717
00:32:00,800 --> 00:32:02,520
Jacob had been given a promise.

718
00:32:02,520 --> 00:32:04,680
His name is changed to Israel.

719
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:08,040
He's been given a promise, and now he's gonna go to Egypt,

720
00:32:08,040 --> 00:32:10,840
and it could be conflicting, but God says, I'll be with you.

721
00:32:10,840 --> 00:32:12,920
I will go down into Egypt with you.

722
00:32:12,920 --> 00:32:15,820
There in Egypt, I will build of thee a great nation.

723
00:32:15,820 --> 00:32:17,840
I will make of thee a great nation,

724
00:32:17,840 --> 00:32:20,960
and God gives that promise, and Jacob goes

725
00:32:20,960 --> 00:32:23,680
as God would command and lead him to do so,

726
00:32:23,680 --> 00:32:27,200
and he has that embrace, and we know that after his death,

727
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:30,600
his children carry him back, even as God said

728
00:32:30,600 --> 00:32:32,880
that they would, and then we come to Joshua,

729
00:32:32,880 --> 00:32:35,720
and we see what's happened in the progress

730
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:38,880
in Israel's history, and after that period of time

731
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:41,420
with Joshua, there's a lot that happens.

732
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:45,480
We have the period of the judges.

733
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:47,520
We have the period in which those folks

734
00:32:48,240 --> 00:32:50,280
that generation that outlived Joshua,

735
00:32:50,280 --> 00:32:51,960
and we see that period of the judges,

736
00:32:51,960 --> 00:32:54,960
and you get into the prophets, and you get into the kings,

737
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:57,000
and you understand all that's taken place,

738
